The petrol price will decrease by 69 cents per litre and diesel will cost you 60 cents less. JOHANNESBURG - The Automobile Association says future predictions of the petrol price remain difficult due to the current political instability, urging motorists to save whatever they can.The petrol price will decrease by 69 cents per litre and diesel will cost you 60 cents less.The association s Layton Beard says this decrease will go a long way, especially during the current economic times. I think the reduction we re seeing now is a welcome relief for motorists, especially as school holidays are underway. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)